// Show the utility of static keywords by taking the example of counter.


class Counter {
  static int count=0;
	Counter() {
	    count++;
      System.out.println(count);
  }
	public static void main (String[] args) 
	{
       System.out.println("Counter values after incrementing:- ");
       Counter c1=new Counter();
       Counter c2=new Counter();
       Counter c3=new Counter();
       Counter c4=new Counter();                             
   }
}

/* When variable ‘counter’ is not taken as static, the updated value of counter is not being preserved and every time it is being updated from 0, the initial value, to 1 
when Counter is being called. But when the variable is being declared as static, the value of counter is incremented considering the updated values each time. */
